text: Greene County is a county on the eastern border of the U.S. state of Tennessee. As of the 2020 census, the population was 70,152. The county seat is Greeneville. The county is named for Nathanael Greene (1742-1786), a major general in the Continental Army from Rhode Island. Greene County was formed in 1783 from the original Washington County. == References == Category:Tennessee counties Category:Tri-Cities, Tennessee
title: Greene County, Tennessee
